title: Forks, SV use OT to move on in sectional playoffs
text:
Forks, SV use OT to move on in sectional playoffs 
By wbng sports October 22, 2015 Updated Oct 22, 2015 at 12:32 AM EDT 
Waverly, NY (WBNG Binghamton) With 20 seconds left in the first overtime session a penalty kick was awarded to Chenango Forks. Nick Markham didn't waste the opportunity as he scored to give the Blue Devils a 2-1 in the Section IV Class B boy's soccer quarterfinals. 
Coulter Wiley scored the other goal as the Blue Devils move on to play top-seed Oneonta in the Section IV semifinals. 
SV beats Dryden in Ot Despite leading 1-0 at the half, Susquehanna Valley needed overtime to get past Dryden, 2-1. 
The Sabers move onto play Windsor in the other Section IV Class B semifinal.
